cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper deals with computational models of cognitive processes and the formalization of the underlying production rule system. It also discusses the translation of these models to a programming language. These topics are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic in computer science (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), cybernetics (cs.CY), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Among these, cs.AI is the most likely category as it deals with the development of intelligent agents and cognitive architectures.
